<img src="/ubbthreads/images/graemlins/grin.gif" alt="" /><br /><br />&gt;I hold no grudge against the Iraqi people, I have no evidence that they are evil in any way. In fact everything I have ever seen about them seems to indicate they are a very nice group of citizens that would actually love to be in a good relationship with the west. I do however hate Saddam, have seen the documented footage of his murdering sprees, seen the paperwork on his son's serial rapist charges and watched him drag his feet and try double talk to delay anything he can. France is not high on my list either do to fact (hell if I know how to spell his name) Sharak and Saddam are long time good if not best friends dating back to the 70's. Anyway, My point is on that, if Bush came to me and said "I want to go blow up Saddam just for the hell of it", my response would have been "HELL YA" <br /><br />I agree that Saddam and his regime need to be taken down, dismantled, burned, the ashes pissed on, and then buried for all eternity, but for the Hell of it? No, you can't go doing things like that without generating a lot of hatred and fear across the globe, just like we're doing now. <br /><br />Like it or not, the US is the super-power in the world right now. We're the big kid on the block. We have responsibilities. We can't go around beating the snot out of other countries just because we want to. That creates unnecessary hostility and it isn't good for the world as a whole. <br /><br />  
