<font class="post">
I just want to give my support to a thread that is more then "my dick is bigger then your dick, etc...". Though this thread has at times wavered that way... it's at least interesting.<br /><br />To throw out some interesting ideas on the issue at hand, I recommend you take a look at the concept of the "Just War". <a href="http://www.utm.edu/research/iep/j/justwar.htm" target="_blank">http://www.utm.edu/research/iep/j/justwar.htm</a><br /><br />This gives a more managable handle on the issues at hand. I do beleive that the Iraqi military is not at all following any  sort of ethical conduct in the war, but I do beleive that the United States did not have enough justification to begin a war. Why haven't we followed the foreign policy we've taken with Iraq with other dictatorships and governments that brutalize their people? If it's simply an issue of non-compliance to the UN, then why isn't this an UN action? There are alot of unanswered questions and the Bush admninistration seems unable or unwilling to answer them clearly and reasonably.<br /><br />-Arravis 
